      "content": "Consuming ibuprofen without consulting a professional can mask pain symptoms that are actually signs of a serious infection like conjunctivitis, causing you to delay critical treatment. Using expired lubricating drops introduces unknown bacteria into your eye, which is a common source of severe, painful infections that can damage your cornea. Ignoring these symptoms risks turning simple dry eyes into a permanent vision problem, and relying on home remedies instead of a diagnosis is far more dangerous than visiting a clinic.",
